I"T<p>Irish Soda Bread - great with a wedge of butter and jam.</p>

<p>This recipe is adapted from a recipe on Easy Peasy Foodie.
<a target="_blank" href="https://www.easypeasyfoodie.com/easy-wholemeal-soda-bread/" class="btn badge-primary">Easy Peasy Foodie →</a></p>

<h1 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h1>

<ul>
  <li>300g Wholewheat Flour</li>
  <li>50g Oats</li>
  <li>120g Natural Yoghurt</li>
  <li>165ml Milk</li>
  <li>1 tsp Bicarbonate of Soda</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/images/recipes/soda-bread/prep.jpg" alt="Soda Bread before the over" />
Soda Bread prepped for the oven.</p>

<h1 id="method">Method</h1>

<ol>
  <li>Preheat the oven to 220°C (200°C Fan).</li>
  <li>Mix the dry ingredients together, Wholewheat Flour (300g), Oats (50g) and Bicarbonate of Sofa (1 tsp).</li>
  <li>Add the milk and the yoghurt to the mix and combine.</li>
  <li>Form the mixture into a round disc (it should be tacky, not wet, add more flour if it’s sticky).</li>
  <li>Cut a deep cross into the disc and dust with a little flour.</li>
  <li>Place on a baking tray or skillet and cook for 30 minutes.</li>
  <li>Remove from the oven and leave to cool before tucking in.</li>
</ol>

